@startuml
title Token Exchange for Org/App Context Switch

actor User
participant "App Service" as APP
participant "Identity Service (AuthN)" as IDN
participant "Authorization Policy (AuthZ/FGA)" as POL

User -> APP: Switch context (audience, context_type, org_id?, env)
APP -> IDN: POST /identity/v1/token/exchange
note over IDN,POL
Monolith now: in-process check via AuthorizationPort
Later: adapter can call /identity/v1/authorize/check
end note
IDN -> POL: AuthorizationPort.check(subject, action, resource, aud, org_id)
POL --> IDN: allow/deny (+ decision_id)
alt allow
  IDN --> APP: exchanged access token (short TTL)
  APP --> User: New active context
else deny
  IDN --> APP: 403 Forbidden
  APP --> User: Context switch denied
end

@enduml
